=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFNoise0_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with complex oscillator character around 54 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 53.5896
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0199
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0115
  pitch_clarity: 29.0115
  inharmonicity: 0.0609
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -17.3996
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFNoise0 Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFNoise0.html
// Tags: LFNoise0, Classes, noise, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ LFNoise0.ar(1000, 0.25) }.play;

// modulate frequency

{ LFNoise0.ar(XLine.kr(1000, 10000, 10), 0.25) }.play;

// as frequency modulator
(
{ SinOsc.ar(
        LFNoise0.ar(4, 400, 450),
        0, 0.2
    )
}.play;
)

// freq is the rate of starting points
{ var freq = 1000; [LFNoise0.ar(freq), Impulse.ar(freq)] }.plot
